=== Similar species ===
While in breeding plumage, the curlew sandpiper can be confused with the [[red knot]], as both are reddish on the belly. Compared to the curlew sandpiper, the red knot is larger, has paler orange-buff underparts rather than rust-colored; has shorter, greenish legs; and is with a stockier bill, as well as a spotted and greyish rump. Compared to the [[red phalarope]], the curlew sandpiper does not have black on the top of the head or a white patch around the face, nor does it have a straight and yellow beak or fully brick-red underparts.{{Sfn|Mlodinow|Medrano|2023|loc=Field Identification § Similar Species}}
