The non-breeding or juvenile plumage looks similar to other species of its genus, ''Calidris'', such as the stilt sandpiper, which lacks the curlew sandpiper's distinctive white wing stripe and has longer, yellow legs and a flatter head, and the dunlin, which has less visible eyebrows and a straighter bill, along with a generally stouter appearance, and wingtips that barely, if at all, extend beyond the tip of its tail.{{Sfn|Mlodinow|Medrano|2023|loc=Field Identification § Similar Species}}

