In juvenile plumage, the curlew sandpiper can be confused most easily with the juvenile female [[ruff (bird)|ruff]], which is similar in body colour and build, though it is darker, larger, and has a shorter bill, and its legs are yellow instead of black. The dunlin also looks similar, but can be slightly more compact in shape and is usually (but not always) shorter-billed; it can easily be distinguished by its streaked breast and flanks, and brown or black spots on the sides of its upper belly.<ref>{{cite book | editor1-last=Cramp | editor1-first=Stanley | editor1-link=Stanley Cramp | year=1983 | chapter=Subfamily Calidrinae | title=Handbook of the Birds of Europe the Middle East and North Africa. The Birds of the Western Palearctic | volume=III: Waders to Gulls | location=Oxford | publisher=[[Oxford University Press]] | isbn=978-0-19-857506-1 | pages=339–340, 356–357, 382–383, 385–386}}; {{cite book |last1=Hayman |first1=Peter |last2=Marchant |first2=John |last3=Prater |first3=Tony |title=Shorebirds |publisher=[[Croom Helm]] |publication-place=London |date=1986 |isbn=978-0-7099-2034-2 |pages=363–387, plates 73–86}}; {{cite book | last1=Svensson | first1=Lars | last2=Mullarney | first2=Killian | last3=Zetterstroem | first3=Dan | title=Collins Bird Guide | publisher=[[William Collins (imprint)|William Collins]] | date=2023 | isbn=978-0-00-854746-2 | pages=152–161|language=en}}; {{cite book |last=Jonsson |first=Lars |title=Birds of Europe |publisher=[[Christopher Helm]] |publication-place=London |date=1992 |isbn=0-7136-8096-2 |pages=216–232|url=https://archive.org/details/birdsofeuropewit0000jons|language=en}}; {{cite book |last1=Harris |first1=Alan |last2=Tucker |first2=Laurel |last3=Vinicombe |first3=Keith |title=The Macmillan Field Guide to Bird Identification |publisher=Macmillan |publication-place=London |date=1989 |isbn=978-0-333-42773-6 |pages=75–82|title-link=The Macmillan Field Guides to Bird Identification|language=en}}; {{cite book |last1=Hume |first1=Rob |last2=Still |first2=Robert |last3=Swash |first3=Andy |last4=Harrop |first4=Hugh |last5=Tipling |first5=David |title=Britain's Birds |publisher=[[Princeton University Press]] |publication-place=Princeton, New Jersey |date=2016 |isbn=978-0-691-15889-1 |pages=194–205|language=en}}</ref>

